	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev&#58; Mr Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">D. Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">In the Episcopal Recorder<lb/> of this city&#44; is an article upon the subject<lb/> of &#8220;<hi rend="underline">The Jews</hi>&#8221; that interested me very much&#44;<lb/> and I would like much to see it republished<lb/> in the Occident with such comments as<lb/> may choose to make&#8212;or the comments<lb/> without the piece.  I would like to see both<lb/> in your <del>paper</del> periodical&#44; <hi rend="underline">first</hi> <sic>becuse</sic> some<lb/> of us have seen it and have hardly known<lb/> what to say or think respecting it&#58; the views<lb/> presented was somewhat new to us&#44;&#8212;and<lb/> <hi rend="underline">secondly</hi>&#44; it is written with so much candor<lb/> and fairness that I think its republication<lb/> as suggested will have a good <sic>effects</sic> upon<lb/> the feelings of Jews and Gentiles towards<lb/> each other.  You will find it in the Episcopal<lb/> Recorder printed by <persName>Stoody<add>&#63;</add></persName> or the <date>2 of August</date> Inst.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Respectfully yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Samuel</persName></p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>Received at the <placeName>Phil</placeName> PO<lb/> under cover from <placeName>Wilkes Barre Pa</placeName><lb/> <date>Aug 8&#47;37</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev&#58; Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>371 Walnut St</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
